com.softwareag.natural.mapconverter.converters

Class TEXTIDConversionListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.softwareag.natural.mapconverter.converters.TEXTIDConversionListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IConversionListener

    public class TEXTIDConversionListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements IConversionListener
    An example listener which generates localization files and corresponding textids.
    It implements the IConversionListener interface:
  • In the start() method it initializes private data structures to collect the textids.
  • In the finish() method it writes the following file: ./multilanguage/en/textidconv.csv.
  • In the startLiteral() method it derives a convenient textid from the name of the passed literal.

      • startFieldTarget

        public void startFieldTarget(IfField field,
                             java.lang.String targetItem,
                             java.util.Map attributeVals)
        Description copied from interface: IConversionListener
        Called when the conversion of a <ifField> for a specific targetitem starts.

        The method is called after the attribute values are resolved according to the conversion rules but before the targetitem is created. Notice that for a single ltLiteral several targetitems can be specified in the conversion rules. In this case this method will be called several times with different targetItem values. The name of the currently processed targetitem is passed to this method.

        Specified by:
        startFieldTarget in interface IConversionListener
        Parameters:
        field - - the field as SDO object
        targetItem - - the name of the targetitem as specified in the conversion rules
        attributeVals - the attribute values

      • startLiteral

        public void startLiteral(LtLiteral literal,
                         java.util.Map attributeVals)
        Description copied from interface: IConversionListener
        Called when the conversion of a <ltLiteral> starts.

        The method is called after the variables and attribute values are resolved according to the default targetitems of the matching rules. The method is called before any targetitem is created.

        Example Usage: A listener can add a textid attribute with the corresponding id as value to the passed attributeVals map. It further can add the text id and translation value to a .csv translation file.
